text.tspan: The vessel shall not be handed over unless "TA -10 - Vessel Handover Checklist" has been completed and express approval isreceived from Head Office.9.3GENERAL DUTIES CONNECTED WITH OWNERS1) Pre-delivery costs for take-over are to be sent one month in advance by accounts department. If take-over is scheduled at a shorterperiod than one month a standard pre -delivery costs shall be proposed by Technical Supt. in consultation with the AccountsDepartment as soon as the owner has confirmed vessel’s management with the company.2) The Superintendent shall prepare the take-over Report within 15 days of takeover date for each vessel coming into management. Adraft report shall be obtained in office within 7 days of takeover of the vessel if Superintendent sails onboard the vessel.3) Complete the pre-delivery/ takeover accounts within 2 months of delivery/ change of management. Keep in mind that especially forsecond-hand vessel takeover the Sale and Purchase transactions are at times delayed due to some unprecedented reasons whichcan lead to huge variances in pre- delivery costs (actual to proposed costs).4) A comprehensive list of reporting required for specific owners should be prepared and posted in the owners’ instructions file forready reference. Owners’ instructions shall be updated as and when some additional requirements are given.9.4DOCUMENTS REQUIRED FOR NEW BUILD VESSELS9.4.1FOR SOPEP / SMPEPList of vessel's plans and drawings:1) General Arrangement Plan2) Capacity Plan3) Midship Section4) Piping Diagram of Bilge, Ballast, Fresh Water and F. O. Line5) Piping Diagram of Oil Transfer System6) Piping Diagram of Bilge Transfer System7) Piping Diagram of Lubricating Oil Transfer System8) Piping Diagram of Air, Sounding and Filling Pipes9.4.2FOR SHIP SECURITY PLAN1) General Arrangement Plan9.4.3BALLAST WATER MANAGEMENT PLAN1) Ballast tank arrangement with ballast capacity plan2) A ballast water piping and pumping arrangement, including air pipes and sounding arrangements3) Ballast water pump capacities9.4.4PANAMA CANAL SOPEPList of certificate: - IOPP certificate9.4.5PANAMA CANAL TRANSITThe Panama Canal Authority (ACP) from 1st September 2012 advises all vessels transiting the Panama Canal for first time toprovide the following documents in electronic format utilizing Word, Excel, PDF, Tiff, Jpeg or similar formats:1) International tonnage certificate 1969 (ITC-69) with calculation sheet.2) PC/UMS Documentation of Total Volume, Suitable Substitute.3) Volume Calculations ( If Available).4) Suez Canal Certificate ( If Available).5) Loadline Certificate (If Multiple Load Lines exist, provide the one with least freeboard).6) Pilot Card ( Vessels speed and general Information).7) Ship Particulars.8) Certificate of Registry.9) Ship Classification Certificate.10)Minimum Crew Safe Manning Certificate.11)International Sewage Pollution Prevention Certificate.12) International Oil Pollution Prevention Certificate.The following drawings (plans) shall be provided in PDF or AUTOCAD format only, in one plan (not sections), in order to allow for
